<meta property="twitter:description" name="description" content="Gina Kolata is a reporter at The Times, focusing on science and medicine. Her training is in science: She studied molecular biology on the graduate level at M.I.T. for a year and a half and has a master&#8217;s degree in applied mathematics from the University of Maryland.
Her work at The Times has led her to be a Pulitzer finalist twice &#8212; for investigative reporting in 2000 and for explanatory journalism in 2010. Other writing awards include ones in 2010 from the Silurian Society for a series on the war on cancer and from The Associated Press Sports Editors for writing about the Caster Semenya intersex controversy at the world track championships.
